U.K. Minister Hunt is ‘Confident’ BSkyB Plan Strengthens Media Plurality

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 
2011-03-30T09:53:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/u-k-minister-hunt-is-confident-bskyb-plan-strengthens-media-plurality.html
The U.K. culture minister  Jeremy
Hunt  said today he is “confident” that News Corp.’s proposed
undertakings in its bid to take over the rest of  British Sky
Broadcasting Group Plc (BSY)  will strengthen media plurality. The U.K.
government is currently considering responses to the
undertakings.  Hunt spoke today at a committee meeting with lawmakers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Browning at 
 jbrowning9@bloomberg.net  